# Project: Acme API

> Vietnamese fintech API. Python 3.11, FastAPI, PostgreSQL. Compliance: PCI-DSS Level 1.

## Stack

- Backend: FastAPI 0.115, SQLAlchemy 2, Alembic
- Tests: pytest, pytest-asyncio
- Lint/format: ruff (line-length 100)
- Package manager: uv (NOT pip, NOT poetry)
- Deploy: AWS ECS Fargate, Terraform

## Commands you'll use often

```bash
uv sync                       # install / update deps
uv run pytest -x              # run tests, stop on first failure
uv run ruff check . --fix     # autofix lint
uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "msg"  # new migration
just deploy-staging           # custom shortcut
```

## Conventions

- All money is `Decimal`, never `float`. Never.
- All DB writes inside `async with session.begin():` — no commits scattered.
- Public API request/response = Pydantic models in `api/schemas/`. ORM models in `db/models/` are NEVER returned over the wire.
- Imports: stdlib → third-party → local, separated by blank lines (ruff handles this).
- Tests live next to code: `services/billing.py` → `services/test_billing.py`.

## Things to NOT do

- ❌ Don't run `uv pip install <pkg>` — add to `pyproject.toml` then `uv sync`.
- ❌ Don't add `print(...)` — use `logger.info(...)` (structlog).
- ❌ Don't add fields to `db/models/` without an Alembic migration.
- ❌ Don't write integration tests against staging DB — use `docker compose up test-db`.
- ❌ Don't commit `.env`, `.env.local`, `.aws/credentials`, anything starting with `key_*`.

## Architecture refs (read instead of asking)

- `architecture.md` — system overview
- `db/MIGRATIONS.md` — migration runbook (downtime windows, rollback procedure)
- `compliance/PCI-CHECKLIST.md` — what's audited, what's gated

## Anti-patterns we've banned

- Sync DB calls in async handlers (perf killer — caught in CR review #4421)
- Catching bare `except:` — wraps DB errors silently (incident 2025-09-12)
- `requests` library for outbound — use `httpx.AsyncClient` for everything

